    <note>Lu(9) Youde [16493] I am assuming that this jinshi was late in life since his mother died in 1198 at age 65. His younger brother, Youzhi [16494], is probably the same person as the homonym, Youzhi, son-in-law of Zhou(1) Ziqiang [16488], based on generational name, probable address and chronological logic (if not brother, then cousin). This Lu(9) lineage is probably related to the Jinhua Lu(9), descendants of the Dongping Lu(9), since Youde was the first Dongyang jinshi and the second Wuzhou jinshi after L?1) Zuqian [7055]. Zhejiang TZ, 127.18a. CBD, 2, 1193.</note>
